result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel V Page was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Incident], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Incident], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • 4th Degree Sexual Assault [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Incident], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3m).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Daniel V Page in court with attorney Michael G. Levine.  Joshua Miles Mathy appeared for the State of Wisconsin for Cindy Davis.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by counsel and defendant.  
AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 15 days time served.  The court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 24 months with the following conditions:
*Defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction consecutive to Count 3.  No good time credit.  Court stayed sentence to be used as sanctions.  
AS TO COUNT 2: 
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 90 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 0 days time served.  The court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 24 months.
AS TO COUNT 3: 
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 0 days time served.  The court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 24 months with the following conditions:
*Defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction consecutive to Count 1.  No good time credit.  Court stayed sentence to be used as sanctions.  

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 3 CONDITION TIME: Court ordered defendant to serve 10 days STRAIGHT time for 1st violation; 25 days STRAIGHT time for 2nd violation; 45 days STRAIGHT time for 3rd violation and balance as STRAIGHT time for 4th violation.

As to all counts:
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Absolute sobriety.
*Random urine screens.
*Domestic violence batterer's intervention
*No contact with Jessica C. without agent's approval.

*Obtain high school diploma or GED.
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy
*Vocational/educational training
*Parenting classes
*Pay restitution in the sum of $36.00 to Crime Victim Compensation Fund.
*Pay all costs and surcharges

As to count 3: Court ordered defendant to provide DNA sample and imposed mandatory surcharge.
As to counts 1 and 2: Court ordered defendant to pay mandatory DNA surcharge.
As to all counts: Defendant to pay DNA surcharges, Domestic  Violence surcharges AND all other costs and surcharges during probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
